stats.def.connectionsByUniqueVisitor: This indicator makes it possible to measure the platform’s usage frequency per unique user over a given period of time.
stats.def.uniqueVisitor: This refers to a user who is identified as unique regardless of the number of times they sign into the platform over a given period.
stats.error.noclassesfound: You must be affiliated with at least one class to see your statistics
stats.error.nonadmlofstructure: You do not have access to the school’s statistics. Please select a class.
stats.export.lightbox.info: Please note: When exporting aggregated data from a main structure, the activity of users who are affiliated with several schools is counted only once.
stats.export.lightbox.tipbox: When exporting aggregated data from a main structure, the activity of users who are affiliated with several schools is counted only once. On the individual school level, this activity is counted for each school with which the users are affiliated.
stats.labels.activatedAccounts: Trend in the number of accounts activated
stats.labels.connectionsByUniqueVisitors: Trend in number of visits per unique visitor
stats.labels.dailyPeak: Number of visits per time slot since 1 September
stats.labels.uniqueVisitors: Trend in number of unique visitors
stats.labels.weeklyPeak: Number of visits per day of the week since 1 September
stats.onboarding.adml.bottomlevelstructu: You can export your school’s data with or without a class-level breakdown.
stats.onboarding.adml.toplevelstructure:
You can export an aggregated or detailed version of the data of your various structures.
Within each of your individual schools, you can also export statistics for each class.
stats.onboarding.content: Explore your various indicators: sign-ins, unique visitors, sign-ins by unique visitors, app access, connector access, most used device, account activation, as well as daily and time-specific traffic peaks.
